  "prompt": "What is the omen behind itchy palms?",
  "response": "The belief that itchy palms are an omen or have specific meanings is rooted in superstition and folklore, and it varies across cultures. Here are some common interpretations:\n\n1. **Left Palm Itching (Receiving Money)**:\n   - In many Western cultures, an itchy left palm is said to signify that you will *receive money* or experience a financial windfall.\n   - Some interpretations suggest that you should rub the palm on wood or let it itch freely to \"let the money come.\"\n\n2. **Right Palm Itching (Giving Money)**:\n   - An itchy right palm is often associated with *losing money* or having to *pay out* money. Some interpretations say it means you will give money to someone or have unexpected expenses.\n\n3. **Other Cultural Beliefs**:\n   - In some traditions, itchy palms are seen as a sign of *guests arriving* or *new opportunities*.\n   - In Chinese superstition, itchy palms might be interpreted as a sign of destiny, with left palm itching indicating good luck and the right palm suggesting challenges ahead.\n\n4. **Medical Perspective**:\n   - From a practical standpoint, itchy palms could simply be caused by dry skin, allergies, or other dermatological conditions. Persistent itching should be checked by a healthcare professional.\n\nUltimately, these interpretations are based on folklore and should be taken with a grain of curiosity rather than as literal predictions!",
